The paper deals with deep learning algorithms for medical image analysis, specifically fetal ultrasound images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel method for representation disentanglement within a multi-task learning framework, which involves the use of deep neural networks and adversarial regularization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks to learn disentangled internal representations, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
